				<title>Tuyển: UNIX - LINUX System Admin</title>
				<description><![CDATA[ <font color='orange'><b><font size='+1'>UNIX System Admin</font></b></font>
<b><font color='orange'>
Job Description</font></b>
This employee, part of the global IT team, would perform all systems administration for the Design Center in Vietnam. 

<b><font color='orange'> Responsibilities</font></b>
•	Perform administration for all Linux compute servers, Windows-based servers and PCs, storage, backup and network infrastructure. 
•	Support applications such as Windows Desktop applications, version control system, and electronic design automation.
•	Provide user support for Windows PCs and Linux servers including all troubleshooting and problem resolution
 Qualifications
•	College degree or equivalent experience in Information Systems, Computer Science, Electrical Engineering
•	4-7 years IT administration experience
•	Strong operating system background in Linux, Solaris, and Windows
•	Strong English skills, both verbal and written
•	Strong troubleshooting and problem solving skills. 
•	Ability to work independently. 
•	Scripting skills.
•	Windows administration (printing, imaging, support, upgrades). 

<b><font color='orange'>Additional skills:</font></b>
The following skill set is highly desirable but not required
•	EDA (Electronic Design Automation) experience
•	Background with GRID computing (LSF, GRID Engine)
•	Network Appliance Fileservers - Veritas Backup - NIS and DNS Administration nice  to have
•	Network and security/firewall experience (Cisco, Checkpoint).

<b><font color='orange'>Salary:</font></b>
Competitive
<font color='orange'><b>
Company Overview:</b></font>
A leader in network and embedded PowerPC processing, optical transport and storage solutions

Designs, develops, markets and supports high-performance integrated circuit (IC) products, embedded processors, and storage components. 

Provides the essential building blocks for the processing, moving and storing of information worldwide

The company blends systems and software expertise with high-performance, high-bandwidth silicon integration to deliver silicon, hardware and software solutions for global wide area networks (WAN), embedded applications, storage area networks (SAN), and high-growth storage markets such as Serial ATA (SATA) RAID. 

Headquarters are located in Sunnyvale, California, USA. Sales and Engineering offices are located throughout the world.

Seeking experienced engineers in software and hardware for the new Design Center located in Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam.  The company also has many entry level full time positions available. These positions will allow recent college graduates to gain on-the-job experiences that compliment their course of study and their skill set. Duties include designing, implementing, programming, debugging, and testing ASICs, hardware and software.


